Nachkriegszeit nicht nur die Art und Weise humanitären und entwicklungspolitischen Engagements, sondern auch die emotionale Dimension humanitären Handelns veränderte. Zum ersten Mal liegt nun eine Untersuchung über die Transformation humanitären Engagements von der Nachkriegszeit bis Anfang der 1990er Jahre vor, die emotions- und wissensgeschichtliche Ansätze verbindet.  aMatthias Kuhnert investigates the logic of humanitarian engagement. The focus of the study is how civil society organizations generate popular support for their activities. Using the example of British NGOs, the author analyzes the ways that humanitarian organizations evoke emotions to help communicate their message and foster popular will to help.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aHumanitarian assistance. 0aNon-governmental organizationsxPublic relationszGreat Britain. 4aDritte Welt. 4aEmotionsgeschichte. 4aEntwicklungspolitik. 4aHumanitarismus. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aDevelopment policy.  aThird World.  ahistory of emotions.  ahumanitarianism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831105302470 cprintz978311052904340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110532500zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110532500zOpen Access70423Coveruh